name: Apartment - 2 bedrooms - hot tub + 1 studio
description:
This is our newly renovated home in Amsterdam noord (close to centre). It's a very cozy place ideal for people that need a good remote working space or a place to stay when visiting the city. The 85m bright apartment consist of 2 studios (one of them has a sofa bed) a big living room (with a projector), equipped kitchen, bathroom with shower, toilet and a minimal bedroom with a nice hot tub. Not your typical AIRBNB house, just our home that we are renting it out occasionally when we are away.

The space
The apartment is spacious but very cosy. There's a great light exposure which makes the space really to pleasant to work and chill at any time of the day.

Guest access
Guests are able to access the whole house.

Other things to note
If you need to work there is a second screen you can use. We have a projector in the living room which is also available. The kitchen is also well equipped and guest are welcome to use the f
neighborhood_overview: The apartment is located in the north side of Amsterdam (12 min bike ride from Central Station). It's quite and there are a  lot of green areas and parks around. Several supermarkets within 5 min walk and bus stop across the road. The Metro is about 10 min bike ride away.
host_about:
We are a couple, Ivano (32, Italy) and Rita (30, Portugal).  
We lived 4 years in Amsterdam, 2 years in Byron Bay, Australia and now we are living in the beautiful Porto.
We are really social, relaxed and we work as creative couple doing design and photography. 
Rita loves yoga and Ivano loves surf. We both are great cookers!

name: Unieke woonark op rustige plek in hartje Adam!
description:
Welkom op onze woonark!
Het rustigste plekje van Amsterdam en toch heel dicht bij alles wat de stad te bieden heeft.
Leven op het water is een bijzonder ervaring wat jullie bezoek aan Amsterdam heel speciaal gaat maken.
Veel verschillende cafe's en restaurants, het Westergasterrein, de Jordaan, het centrum en de Foodhallen zijn allemaal op loopafstand te bereiken.
En toch voelt het op de boot alsof je even weg van alles bent.
De perfecte mix voor een verblijf in onze mooie stad!

The space
De woonark heeft een oppervlakte van 65m, verdeeld in 3 grote ruimtes.
Bij binnenkomst loop je over een terras over het water naar de ingang van de ark. Aan de rechterkant bevindt zich de woonkamer voorzien van bank, tv en boekenkast. De woonkamer loopt over in een open keuken waar je heerlijk kan dineren met zicht op het water. Doordat deze ruimtes in elkaar over lopen geeft het een groots en open gevoel!
Via de keuken kom je in de slaa
neighborhood_overview:
De woonark ligt in de fijne en gezellige wijk Westerpark. Het park en bijhorend Westergasterrein vol leuke en speciale horecagelegenheden ligt op een loopafstand van 10 minuten.
Tevens grenst de ligplaats van de woonark aan de wijk Oud-West waar ook een grote verscheidenheid aan winkels, cafe's, restaurants en cullture hotspots te vinden zijn. En waar niet te vergeten de Food en Filmhallen zijn!
Daarnaast ben je in nog geen 10 minuten lopen in de Jordaan.
Mocht je de welbekende musea van Amsterdam willen bezoeken op het Museumplein dan ben je daar in 10 minuten met tram 3.
host_about: Een nette vriendelijke jongeman. Goed met mensen en ben erg netjes. Op zoek naar rustige plekken.

description:
Guest access
DIRECTIONS TO LIGHT TRAVELIN,

FROM SCHIPHOL AIRPORT:

There goes a bus from the airport directly to the Museumplein.
Amsterdam Airport Express (bus 397) about 20 minutes drive.
Tickets available at the bus are around 6,50 euro. Cash is not accepted on the bus, payments are with a bankcard.

About the ticket at the bus, 397 platform B17 to 19

Tickets could be purchased at the driver with pin/bank card or credit card.

Also there are e-tickets online available,
there is also a machine on the platform B19 where you
could buy a ticket for bus 397


1. The bus goes about every 10 minutes on a normal schedule.

2. The bus is in front of the Airport, just follow the signs it is easy to find.
You need to get off the bus at the Museumplein.

3.From the Museumplein it is a 5 minute walk to the accommodation.

description:
Welcome to my home!
My super cozy apartment is located right next to Rembrandt Park, in De baarsjes, a trendy & up-and-coming neighborhood, still central in Amsterdam but away from the annoying tourists places. This is the real Amsterdam.

The apartment is located just a few seconds walk from the beautiful Rembrandt Park.
It is still short distance from most of the city.

5 minutes to Oud west.

A bike rental is located right across the street.

The space

It has one bedroom, which faces the garden so it's very very quite for sleeping, and in the morning the sun shines right in the garden. Lovely.

The living space is quite spacious and it has speakers for music, cozy lightning, curtains for privacy (not a given in Amsterdam) and Smart TV.
The sofa also can turn
neighborhood_overview:
Rembrandt Park is one of the main parks in Amsterdam (together with Vondel Park and Westerpark). Of the 3, it is the least touristy park, which makes it very pleasant for a stroll without the horde of people like in other places.

Rembrandt Park is in the area called: De Baarsjes.
De Baarsjes is one of the most up-and-coming neighborhoods in Amsterdam.
Here you can now find a wide variety of trendy coffees and shops. The trendy food halls where you can eat or shop are within walking distance.

Besides the many shops and bars you can also enjoy recreation in the area such as the Rembrandtpark or the Erasmuspark. In the summer you can sit at the waterfront with a drink or go to the nearby Vondelpark.
Most of the people living in De Baarsjes are in their 20s and 30s.

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam Oost is de fijnste buurt van Amsterdam! Het Oosterpark is op loopafstand en het groene hart van de buurt. Er wordt gesport, gewandeld, en enorm genoten van de zon en het groen. Er omheen zijn talloze restaurantjes, cafe's en koffietenten te vinden. Direct bij ons om de hoek heb je al meer dan 3 koffietentjes die allemaal de lekkerste koffie verkopen. De eerste Oosterparkstraat en de eerste van Swindenstraat zijn bruisende winkelstraten in de multiculturele buurt die Oost is. Als je de andere kant op gaat ben je in no time bij de Amstel rivier, waar geflaneerd wordt langs het water. Op zomerse dagen springt iedereen in het water en kan je er heerlijk zwemmen. Ook hier zijn allerlei cafeetjes en restaurantjes. Als je de Amstel oversteekt ben je in de welbekende buurt de Pijp, met de Albert Cuijpmarkt, het Sarphatipark, en talloze eet en drinkgelegenheden. Ook het centrum van de stad is op loopafstand, of te bereiken met de metro, die om de hoek van het huis een halte heeft.

name: Charming captain's cabin on historic ship De Hoop
description:
We would like to welcome you on board for a unique stay in the captain's cabin of our ship De Hoop. Once an active cargo boat that transported goods and supplies along the Dutch waterways, De Hoop is currently enjoying her well deserved retirement and one hundredth birthday in 2022. De Hoop is perfectly located for those who wish to experience the best of both worlds. You’ll wake up with the serenity of the water, whilst being just a 15 min tram ride from Amsterdam city.

The space
Private, authentic and charming captain's cabin with a queen sized bed (140x200) and storage for luggage and clothes.

A new bathroom with shower, toilet, sink, shampoo, hairdryer & bath robes. A living room with dining table for 2, sofa, TV, Bose speaker, board games and small kitchen area with fridge, coffee machine & kettle (no cooking station). Authentic captains hut with bench and beautiful view.

A communal terrace is available in front of the boat on the jett
neighborhood_overview:
IJburg is a charming, safe and mostly residential neighbourhood which is especially popular for those who enjoy modern architecture and urban design. It's also a perfect location for water sports enthusiasts with options for kayaking, hiking, cycling, windsurfing and paddle boarding amongst others. The area offers a range of cafes, restaurants and bars for those looking for somewhere to enjoy a quiet drink.

During the summer there are two small local beaches including a beach club to enjoy in the summer months, as well as several nature spots where you can walk or cycle and take in the scenery.

You can jump off the boat for a swim or take a walk along the water to IJburg beach which is just 2km away. The city centre is just a 15 min tram ride away from our ship.
host_about:
Hi, we are Lydia and Uhuru a Dutch-UK couple who recently embarked on this exciting adventure of living on a ship.

We would be delighted to share this charming way of living with you and look forward to hopefully welcoming you on board soon!

neighborhood_overview:
Amsterdam De Pijp, straight south of the city center—a one-time working-class area now bursting with diverse restaurants, hip shops, and beatnik charm.

Lose yourself for hours in Amsterdam’s lively Latin Quarter, with its colourful mix of cuisines, terraces and convivial cafés. From the beautiful landscaped gardens of Sarphatipark to the famous Albert Cuypmarkt street market, De Pijp oozes beatnik flair from every angle, and is has been a popular haunt for creatives, students and bohemian spirits since the 60s.

neighborhood_overview:
Situated on the canal, in one of Amsterdam's trendiest neighborhoods. Jordaan is a district in the city center of Amsterdam, originally a working-class neighborhood, but it has now become one of the most expensive, upscale locations of the city. It is known for its beautiful 17th-century houses, popular bars, restaurants, street markets, art galleries, designer boutiques and original shops. The Jordaan is clustered between the four canals of Prinsengracht, Lijnbaansgracht, Passeerdersgracht and Brouwersgracht, on the west side of Amsterdam’s main ring of canals (called the grachtengordel). When in Amsterdam, it is a must to stroll through the little streets and canals.
Every Saturday there is the Lindengracht Market, around the corner of the apartment, with amazing flowers, food and local specialties. It is within walking distance of all the famous tourist attractions, such as the Amsterdam canals, Nine Streets (shopping area), the Anne Frank House, The Dam, Leidse Square and Am

neighborhood_overview:
De Baarsjes is very much on the rise as an up-and-coming Amsterdam neighbourhood with a population that is both young and multicultural. Situated remarkably close to the city centre and with plenty of green, the area is attractive for families, artists and young professionals alike.

Area
De Baarsjes is west of Oud West on the other side of the major waterway Kostverlorenvaart. It is bound into a triangle of sorts by the A10 ring highway to the west and Jan van Galenstraat to the north.

History
Built during the first half of the 20th century along a tram line that brought commuters to the city centre, De Baarsjes was part of idealistic ‘Plan West’ expansion plan formulated by the architect HP Berlage who himself designed the main square Mercatorplein. As it was mostly built before WWII, it was all built to last so when it came to urban renewal in the 1990s, most buildings were renovated and not razed to the ground. description:
Enjoy the full comfort of a unique city residence with a garden, located in a most charming street in the very heart of the city.
The bright and open space of this loft will welcome and excite you time and over again.

The space
I want to share a feeling of "excitement" in this loft. The bright and open space will draw you in from the moment you enter, and make you eager to stay and explore.

The large front window looking onto the street is connected with the garden at the back and the amount of daylight that comes in at any time of the day gives an airy and spacious feeling. Through the entrance, hall small staircases lead to the upper and lower floor, while the openness and interconnectivity of the space reinforces a true loft vibe.

neighborhood_overview:
The "Weteringbuurt" or Wetering quarter is a most charming neighborhood of Amsterdam. Neighbors sit outside and have a drink in front of their door, chitchat with the locals, and visitors alike. Located in the drop-dead centre of the city, in a side street of Prinsengracht and in the vicinity of the famous Rijksmuseum, it is surrounded by canals, cafés and restaurants and everything is on walking distance. Quite literally, it is the epicentre of Amsterdam, meaning that wherever you want to go, it will all be very close.

Moreover, it is a very safe and quiet street, close enough to the all the bars & restaurants, but far enough from the noise. A perfect location to explore Amsterdam.
host_about:
Hello, nice to meet you! I'm here because I love to share experiences, travels, stories and live & laugh with people from all over the globe. 

Languages and cultures are my passion so I try to grasp every opportunity to explore unknown terrain, meet new people and find beauty in the smallest details.

I am guided in life by the belief that we are all created free and equal, no matter of where we come from, what we believe in, who we love or what we look like. 

“The future is not some place we are going, but one we are creating. The paths are not to be found, but made. And the activity of making them changes both the maker and the destination.” - John H. Schaar

You can write me in English, French, Dutch, German and Bosnian.

name: Sunny appartment in De Pijp, Amsterdam
description:

Located on the first floor in a quiet street of bustling De Pijp, the appartment is fully equiped for a comfortable city trip in Amsterdam.

The space
Located in a quiet street of De Pijp, you can easily reach the appartment in 7min from Amsterdam Centraal station and in 30min from Schiphol airport with public transport.

Via the large staircase, you can access the appartment located on the first floor. You enter a large living room area. neighborhood_overview:
De Pijp is one of the cutest and most typic area of Amsterdam. you can find there a lot of bar, restaurants and little shops.
Albert Cuyp Market is only 7 minutes walking distance, available Monday to Saturday from 9 to 5. You have to go try the fresh Stroopwaffels (waffle with caramel).
The museum district is 20min walking or easy to reach via tram 3 from the appartment. You can visit there Van Gogh Museum, Rijksmuseum, Moco or the contemporary museum Stedelijk.
Further with tram 3, you can reach Jordaan and the cute little streets of de 9 Straatjes.
With the metro 52 you are at Centraal station in 10minutes from the appartment.

This neighbourhood is amazing and very vibrant. Right downstairs from the building you will find the Amsterdamse Poort with plenty of shops. You have Lidl, Albert Heijn and Vomar (for groceries), but also a local market twice a week and plenty of local stores selling groceries.

In addition you will find all sorts of other shops (H&M, Blokker) and restaurants, from cafes to KFC and McDonalds, or Asian takeaway.

neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood is very peaceful, safe and family-friendly. It has a bit of a village vibe inside a bigger city. The direct neighborhood is considered upscale, with lots of families with children living in the area.

There is a playground directly around the corner, with a picnic area and the possibility to swim in the dock during summer.

There is also a traditional Dutch snackbar (Febo), and a bike rental (Halfords) just around the corner and an outisde neighborhood (farmers') market every Wednesday, Friday and Saturday, called 'Pekmarkt'.

The market, and closest supermarket, grocery shops and stores are located at Mosveld, a 10-15 minute walk or a 3-4 minute bike ride.
The opening hours from the supermarket (Albert Heijn) are 7-22 and 8-22 during the weekend, also on Sunday!

It is very easy to get to the house from the Central Station.

Once you cross the IJ canal, it is 10-15 minute walk or 4 minute bike ride to the location

name: Stijlvol & luxe appartement in levendige buurt!
description:
Welkom in mijn gezellige appartement gelegen in Amsterdam-Oost. Dit luxe appartement is zeer recent gerenoveerd en voorzien van alle gemakken. Woonkamer met Frans balkon, volledig uitgeruste keuken, tv (Netflix), luxe badkamer met riant bad, comfortabel bed, balkon aan de achterzijde, aparte werkplek.

De buurt is levendig maar rustig met veel trendy bars en restaurants in de buurt. Gemakkelijke toegang tot het stadscentrum (15 min). Op loopafstand van de Amstel, Pijp en naast het Oosterpark.

Guest access
Toegang tot alle ruimtes.

Other things to note
Het appartement is geschikt voor 2 gasten. Op verzoek en tegen een meerprijs is verblijf voor 3 of 4 gasten ook mogelijk. In de werkkamer staat een slaapbank, die kan worden uitgeklapt tot een (klein) tweepersoonsbed.

License number
0363 3D2D 5600 F462 6C3A
neighborhood_overview: Oost wordt vaak vergeleken met Quartier Latin in Parijs en is een van de populairste buurten in Amsterdam en een van de meest gewilde buurten om te wonen. De buurt verspreidt zich rond Oosterpark, een groot groen gebied met moderne sculpturen, vijvers en wandelpaden. In de nabij omgeving vind je het Tropenmuseum, Carré theater en Artis de Zoo. Eveneens op loopafstand vind je veel trendy bars en uitgaansgelegenheden rondom het Beukenplein, de Wibautstraat en de hippe Javastraat. Het appartement ligt zeer dicht bij de prachtige Amstel en de bruisende Pijp. Het stadscentrum is slechts 15 minuten lopen. Mocht je iets verder weg moeten? Het appartement licht zeer dicht bij de metro.
host_about: Hi ik ben Wiecher! Lang getwijfeld of ik mijn gloednieuwe appartement voor verhuur ter beschikking wil stellen, maar nu toch de stap gezet. name: Beautiful condo in city centre of Amsterdam
description:
Our spacious appartement is located in a beautiful alley in the Jordaan, next to one of Amsterdam’s most prestigious canals ‘Prinsengracht’. The famous ‘Noordermarkt’, with one its finest street markets on Saturday, is -literally- just around the corner.

In 5-10 minutes walking distance you are at Central Station, can visit the Anne Frank House or the Nine Streets with its famous boutique shops.

The space
Our place (100m2) has everything you need to enjoy Amsterdam to its fullest. We have a balcony facing South, a rooftop terrace of 18m2 with panoramic view over amsterdam. Next to that we have a separate office space. We also have amenities like a Quooker (instant boiling water), 2 fridges, a wine cooler, clothing closet, dishwasher, washing machine, tumble dryer, iron & ironing board, airfryer, combo oven / microwave. Moreover, we have a large tv with Apple TV & Netflix and WiFi. You can enjoy your home cooked meals either at the bar of our kitchen i
neighborhood_overview: The famous Jordaan neighbourhood is a former working-class bastion, renowned for tight community bonds, radical politics and a love for drink and over-the-top sing-a-longs. Gentrification of decades past has attracted more galleries, restaurants, concept stores and vintage boutiques to its flowery streets, but there is undeniably still a distinct atmosphere to enjoy here. Discover lively café terraces, historic brown bars, the bustling Noordermarkt, elm-lined canal streets, quirky museums and of course, the Anne Frank Huis.

neighborhood_overview:
Our area is one of the best in Amsterdam, because it is part of the city center, but just outside the tourist bustle of the center. You can easily reach the old center by bike or even by walking.
The main street for daily shopping is around the corner. There you will find several restaurants, takeaways and supermarkets. Nearby amenities include breakfast cafes, takeout/delivery stores, supermarkets and restaurants, all within a ten-minute walk.

Our part of town was built in the late 19th century to house workers. It is famous for its particularly beautiful architecture called "Amsterdam School". The corresponding museum in that style is around the corner.

neighborhood_overview:
Het appartement bevind zich in een van de leukste wijken van Amsterdam: de pijp! De straat zelf is lekker rustig, maar op loopafstand vind je de bekende Albert Cuyp markt (350 m), waar je ook talloze leuke bars en restaurantjes kan vinden.

Ook onze favoriete bar- en winkelstraat De Utrechtsestraat is om de hoek (450 m), Daar vind je niet alleen allemaal leuke barretjes en boetieks, maar beginnen ook de historische grachten zo kenmerkend voor Amsterdam. Hier vind je ook het koninklijke theater Carré en de Hermitage.

Om de hoek zit een hotel waar je fietsen kan huren. De perfect manier om Amsterdam te ontdekken!

Bij de Amstel (400 m) zit een verhuur voor bootjes, zodat je als een echte Amsterdammer de grachten kan verkennen.

Voor meer tips, schroom niet om ons een berichtje te sturen!

- Een apotheek
- Meerdere beauty salons

neighborhood_overview:
Located in a quiet neighborhood, but at the same time in the city center!
Within 5/15 min walking distance you can find a lot of interesting places such as Brewery 't Ij near the windmill, the Oosterpark, Artis Zoo and it's lovely 'Plantage area'. But also towards Amsterdam Central train station you can find science museum Nemo, the National Maritime Museum and the 'Marineterrein'. This used to be a Maritime area, but is now a cool swimming place with restaurants, ideal for summer!

Furthermore in the area you will find a lot of different restaurants and cafe's within walking distance. There is a good public transport connection towards central station and station Muiderpoort.
And for the daily groceries there are 3 supermarkets within 5 minutes walking distance.
A great location!
host_about:
Hi! My name is Annelieke and together with my boyfriend Ramin I am living in the city center of the most beautiful city of the world, Amsterdam!
I grew up in a small village in the eastern part of the Netherlands, but live in A'dam since 2007.
I really enjoy living in this city and love to go out for drinks or dinner, strolling around, visiting musea, swim in the canals, and of course biking! 
Cycling through the city every time puts a smile on my face, the city is beautiful during each season and I am happy to life here!

Your 'harbor' will be the lively center of Amsterdam - right in the middle of it. Everything (really everything) you are looking for in Amsterdam is reachable by foot. That being said it is obvious that this is maybe not the best choice if you are looking for a quite place in nature with no one around, here you will always have some people around. However, we have always experienced it as a pretty quiet area in the evenings.

- National opera and ballet

- Artis Zoo
- Zuiderkerk + Seven sisters (iconic Amsterdam view)
- Museumsquare (~ 15 minute walk)

- Historic canals (UNESCO world heritage) (all around you).

neighborhood_overview:
De Staatsliedenbuurt in Amsterdam is een hele levendige, bruisende buurt die vlakbij het centrum van de stad ligt. Er staan vele wat kleinere oude arbeiderswoningen en maakt het een karakteristiek deel van Amsterdam. Veel van deze woningen zijn modern en gezellig met authentieke elementen. De Staatsliedenbuurt is bijna geheel omgeven door water, met de Westergasfabriek aan de overkant van de Haarlemmerweg aan de noordkant. In het Westerpark en rondom de Westergasfabriek zijn veel leuke cafeetjes en restaurantjes te vinden. Ook in de Staatsliedenbuurt zelf zijn veel leuke en hippe tentjes te vinden, verspreid door de buurt. Op het Van Limburg Stirumplein kun je lekker op een terrasje genieten van een biertje of kop koffie. Alles op loopafstand te bereiken.

Het IJ en CS zijn vlakbij en daarmee is deze buurt goed bereikbaar. Er zijn tal van historische gebouwen in deze buurt te vinden. Het 19e-eeuwse stratenpatroon en de pleintjes maken het een authentieke Amsterdamse buurt.

Amsterdam is a relatively small city with an extensive offering of shopping, food, entertainment and culture. So, everyone has easy access to everything. There are not that many locations, however, where so much is reachable within minutes of walking. Our Town House is positioned in the middle of the Western canal area, a location that might be optimal in terms of access:

Nine streets
The ‘SOHO’ of Amsterdam, the ‘nine streets’, can be found in the side streets of the Keizersgracht at each side of the house. These streets hold many of Amsterdam’s interesting and fashionable stores (and restaurants), and on the weekends create a very pleasant buzz of people strolling around or sitting at the side walk cafes.

Jordaan
De Jordaan, generally considered the most picturesque of the Amsterdam neighbourhoods, and home to numerous restaurants, bars and small shops, starts one block away from the house.

Hey,

Welcome to Amsterdam, my idea of a user-friendly city!

Amsterdam is a lovely place to spend a few days in, particularly if you will be able to dive in to the local rhythm of life.

The apartment is located in Oud-Zuid which is one of the boroughs of Amsterdam. The Museum Quarter (Museumplein) with the Stedelijk Museum, Van Gogh Museum, and the Rijksmuseum, belongs to Oud-Zuid.

Oud-Zuid is home to Amsterdam's most luxury shopping street -- the PC Hooftstraat -- which features high-end clothing (Chanel, Gucci, Hermés, Louis Vuitton), jewelry (Chopard, Cartier) and specialty (Mont Blanc, Henckels) stores, as well as several boutiques selling more luxury labels.
The Van Baerlestraat features chic names like Pauw and Vanilia. Beethovenstraat, along the eastern border of this neighborhood, boasts a row of women's, men's and children's chic shops. Don't miss Cornelis Schuytstraat and its trendy boutiques and home stores for a special Dutch outfit or gift.

name: Dijkwoning met tuin in Amsterdam Noord
description:
Op zoek naar een rustige, groene plek op 25 minuten van het centrum van Amsterdam? Jullie zijn welkom in onze sfeervolle dijkwoning in Amsterdam Noord. Begin de dag met een koffietje in de tuin. Met de fiets rij je in een kleine 10 minuten naar het levendige NDSM-terrein met terrassen, restaurants, ateliers, kunst en de gratis pont naar het centrum van Amsterdam. Met de auto rij je in 30-35 minuten naar omliggende plaatsen zoals Haarlem en het strand.

The space
Via de voordeur kom je via de hal binnen in de woonkamer annex keuken en eetkamer. Het typische van een dijkhuis is dat de tuin een verdieping lager ligt. Op deze verdieping is een washok met wasmachine en droger, de 'master bedroom' met open badkamer, een aparte wc en de toegang tot de tuin.

In de groene tuin ligt een trampoline en staat een thuinhuis met veranda waar je kunt chillen, bbq-en en kijken naar de meerkoetjes in de sloot.

De trap vanuit de hal naar boven brengt je bij
neighborhood_overview: Het leuke aan Amsterdam-Noord is de mix van mensen. In deze buurt wonen gezinnen, ondernemers, ambachtslui en studenten. Het is in onze buurt niet toeristisch maar hoe dichter je bij het water (het IJ) komt, hoe meer er te beleven valt. Zoals het voormalige scheepswerven terrein NDSM, ook wel het meest creatieve stukje Amsterdam genoemd. Een chaotische maar originele mix van restaurants, kunst, graffiti, pizzeria, terrassen en de pannenkoekenboot. Op loopafstand van de accommodatie is een klein winkelcentrum met oa een supermarkt en drogisterij. Wil je de natuur in? Met de auto ben je in 10 minuten in recreatiegebied het Twiske of in 35 minuten op het strand. Een avondwandeling over de dijk langs woonboten en dijkhuizen is prachtig en fascinerend tegelijk.
host_about:
Samen met mijn drie dochters (en poes Babs) wonen wij sinds drie jaar in dit knusse huis met groene tuin. Het huis is een echt gezinshuis met 3 beschikbare slaapkamers, genoeg speelgoed, knutselmateriaal en een pizzaoven om ook een avond lekker thuis te blijven. Wil je op pad? Met de auto zit je binnen 4 minuten op de ring, parkeren is hier gratis en met de fiets sta je binnen 10 minuten op de pont naar Amsterdam Centraal. 

Omdat dit ons eigen huis is vind ik het fijn om jullie eerst wat beter te leren kennen. Je kunt dus niet direct reserveren, maar ik reageer zo snel als mogelijk. Nog vragen? Aarzel niet om ze te stellen.

Perfect for couples or individuals who want to stay in a calm area yet be close to Amsterdam city center.

name: Bright apartment with balcony & parkview - de Pijp
description:
Located in the heart of Amsterdam's hippest neighbourhood. Experience outside, inside, open the balcony doors and watch the bikes and trams pass by from in between the tree tops.
This is an ideal apartment for travellers that want to work remote as it features a stylish corner with an adjustable desk and monitor.
In for a drink or a bite? Across the street there is a cosy restaurant. In for a walk? Within a few steps you are at the entrance of the vibrant Sarphatipark.

License number
0363 B3F7 2BB2 EBDE A6EB
neighborhood_overview:
In essence De Pijp is an urban area demarcated by the beloved canals with at its center a green oasis, the most intensively visited park of Amsterdam, the Sarphatipark, which you will live right next to. It can be seen as one of the most authentic area of Amsterdam, where you can actually still encounter locals, who refer to it as the hippest area the city.

One block after the park you can find the Albert Cuyp market, Amsterdam’s most famous market, originated in 1905, here you can experience an authentic Amsterdam atmosphere, humor and “gezelligheid” in the streets. It opens in the morning and closes in the afternoon each and every day, six days a week for you to try fresh stroopwafels.

7 minutes by tram to the West is the Museum Quarter area, which is home to the three most important museums in the Netherlands: the Rijksmuseum, the Stedelijk Museum and the Van Gogh Museum. It also includes the majestic Concertgebouw and the elegant P.C. Hooftstraat and Van Bae
host_about: Loves to travel, in particular hearing the stories of local people, experiencing their culture and tasting their cuisine.

name: Stylish city apartment with roof terrace!
description:
This stylish city apartment is one of the best.

It has 2 bedrooms and a large roof terrace with a gorgeous view!

The apartment is located in de Pijp, one of the best areas in Amsterdam.

Within walking distance you find cafes, restaurants, coffee places, supermarkets.
Museum square is 7 min away on foot; you'll find several museums there (Van Gogh, Rijksmuseum, Stedelijk), as well as the concert hall (Concertgebouw) and green area that often hosts events in the summer.

License number
0363A47BC6A37A9033E6
neighborhood_overview:
Just a short tram ride south of Centraal Station takes you into one of the most cosmopolitan and vibrant districts of Amsterdam. Welcome to de Pijp.

De Pijp is brimming with fantastic cafés, restaurants, coffee shops and bars. Of course, a visit to Amsterdam wouldn’t be the same without a trip to the Albert Cuypmarket, flanked by over 100 shops. If you wander down Albert Cuypstraat and Ferdinand Bolstraat, the main streets in de Pijp , you'll find many exotic and authentic Syrian, Moroccan, Surinamese restaurants, to name but a few, and a typical Amsterdam pub is located on almost every corner.

Also in abundance are Surinamese, Spanish, Indian and Turkish delicatessens and grocery stores.

Situated in the chic and upmarket Amsterdam Zuid area, close to public transport (1 short tram ride into town), shops, bars, parks, and nearby supermarkets. Zuidas, the business district is nearby and the location is easily reached from Schiphol Airport. Walking distance to the well know Museum Quarter and Pijp and close to the centre of town. A light and airy apartment where you can hear birds singing when you wake up in the morning - so quiet you can't quite believe you are in the city.

The space
Ground Floor apartment with a large and spacious sitting room / dining room and kitchen open planned. This leads off to a small sunny terrace where you get the sunshine all day and enjoy a coffee or drink and if its really warm, eat your dinner outside. One double room is on the ground floor and has double doors onto a small balcony so you can enjoy hearing the birds when you wake up. The other double bedroom is below, which you can access easily from the hallway

neighborhood_overview:
Just a five-minute walk down the Damrak from Centraal Station takes you into this jam-packed square, jostling with locals and tourists day and night. Whatever the weather, there is always something going on.

With the Jordaan and Nine streets at a walking distance of just 3 minutes the apartment is close to the Anne Frank museum.

There are food stalls, restaurants and shopping malls, including the trendy Bijenkorf and Magna Plaza. And the Amsterdam Diamond Centre. Such is the popularity of Dam Square that you might even have to wait for a seat at one of the many cafe's and bars.

But without doubt, of all the attractions in Dam Square, Royal Palace (Koninklijk Palace) is quite literally the jewel in the crown. Although no longer home to the Dutch Royal family, this grand 17th century building is still used to hold official receptions. Opposite the Royal Palace you will see the Hotel Krasnapolsky. neighborhood_overview:
The Borneo-island is a peninsula in the Eastern Harbour District. An area known for its architecture and urban planning. You can take beautiful walks in a decor of history, contemporary architecture and typical Dutch harbour landscape.
15-20 minutes from the busy city center you will find peace and wide views over the water. Children still play on the streets because there is little traffic. When the weather is nice residents quickly come outside to sit on the sidewalks with a drink and a bite, having a chat with their neighbors. It is a jovial and cosy neighborhood where it’s still normal to great each other. In summertime people cool down in and on the water, with a SUP (which you can rent down the block), canoes and small boats, and of course it's wonderful to take a swim in the natural water, and the cold water lovers even swim whole year round.

name: Comfortabele gezinswoning in Amsterdam-Noord
description:
Een fijn huis voor een gezin met jonge kinderen. Op 10 minuten fietsafstand van het centrum van Amsterdam en met een bushalte om de hoek. Dicht bij een park, een bos, veel restaurants. Maar ook niet ver van waterland, een van de mooiste natuurgebieden van Nederland. Een opkomende buurt in Amsterdam, in een huis dat van alle gemakken is voorzien.

neighborhood_overview: Het huis staat in de buurt Tuindorp-Buiksloot. Dat is een wijk met arbeiderswoningen uit de jaren 1930 in Amsterdam-Noord. Noors is een opkomende buurt met veel ruimte voor leuke, vernieuwende horeca. De wijk ligt tussen een mooi stadspark; het Noorderpark, en een klein bos; het Vliegenbos. De verbinding tussen het centrum en noord gaat via een veerpont, die is op 10 minuten fietsafstand van ons huis. Met de metro, 5 minuten lopen, ben je in no time in het centrum. Als je de andere kant op fietst ben je zo in Waterland, een prachtig beschermd natuurgebied.

neighborhood_overview:
OUD-ZUID - OLD SOUTH
Just outside the cultural heart of Amsterdam lies the posh neighborhood of Oud-Zuid, with its ravishing villas and tranquil curving streets. The Oud-Zuid is arguably the elegant heart of Amsterdam, and is one of the city’s most prestigious cultural districts.

Amsterdam’s elegant Oud-Zuid (Old-South) was developed over a century ago as a cultural gateway to the city, at the tip of what was previously a boggy polder. It’s home to Rijksmuseum, Stedelijk Museum, and Van Gogh Museum – all of which exhibit the highlights of Western art. The nearby Vondelpark – created in the style of an English landscape garden – is the city’s most popular playground and is a magnet for picnickers and visitors who flock in their droves during the summer months to the numerous outdoor performances that take place there.

Museums, concerts and galleries

neighborhood_overview:
The Jordaan is possibly the most famous neighbourhood in the Netherlands. Akin to the reputation enjoyed by London’s Cockneys, this once working-class bastion was renowned for tight community bonds, radical politics and a love for drink and over-the-top sing-a-longs. Gentrification of decades past has attracted more galleries, restaurants, specialty shops and upwardly-mobile residents to its scenic streets but there’s undeniably still a distinct atmosphere to be enjoyed here.

The Jordaan begins at Brouwersgracht, just west of the Amsterdam Central Station and arches around the western side of Canal Ring between Prinsengracht and Lijnbaansgracht before ending at Leidsegracht. The area north of Rozengracht is a more ‘touristy’ and commercial section, although the quieter area to the south is no less scenic.

AMSTERDAM CENTRUM - CITY CENTER + CANAL DISTRICT

neighborhood_overview:
Amsterdam east is a buzzing neighborhood, close to the city center and Javastraat, with loads of little restaurants, bars and cafe's. The street my apartment is on is quiet and relaxed though, so you can come home after a day out and about and relax.

The tram isn't that far, about a 7 min walk to catch tram 14 into town. Subway is about a 15 min walk, closest bus and tram about 5 - 10 mins walk.

The eastside used to be the harbor district of Amsterdam and there is water all around, giving it a laidback vibe where you can have loads of great walks. The front of the apartment overlooks the east of Amsterdam, with no large buildings blocking the view over the city.

Gyms, supermarkets, shops and any type of entertainment (zoo, cinema, museums etc) are all a quick bike ride or tram away.

neighborhood_overview:
OUD-ZUID - OLD SOUTH
Just outside the cultural heart of Amsterdam lies the posh neighborhood of Oud-Zuid, with its ravishing villas and tranquil curving streets. The Oud-Zuid is arguably the elegant heart of Amsterdam, and is one of the city’s most prestigious cultural districts.

Amsterdam’s elegant Oud-Zuid (Old-South) was developed over a century ago as a cultural gateway to the city, at the tip of what was previously a boggy polder. It’s home to Rijksmuseum, Stedelijk Museum, and Van Gogh Museum – all of which exhibit the highlights of Western art. The nearby Vondelpark – created in the style of an English landscape garden – is the city’s most popular playground and is a magnet for picnickers and visitors who flock in their droves during the summer months to the numerous outdoor performances that take place there.

neighborhood_overview:
Geuzenveld is a calm and safe neighborhood in Amsterdam, very close to the neighborhoods of West and Central. It is well connected to the city center in 30 minutes, with both direct tram (number 13) and bus (number 21). It is possible to go by bike in less than 20 minutes to iconic places as Westerpark or Ana Frank's House.
Close by there is the train station of Sloterdijk that connects you with other cities in the Netherlands as Haarlem, the Hague, Delft or Utrecht.
In the neighborhood itself there are all kinds of supermarkets, shops and some food places. It is surrounded by nature and canals. There is an amazing natural parks and a forest within 10 minutes walking distance.

name: Roof-terrace apartment, quiet street, trendy area
description:
I love my bright, top-floor apartment, and I hope you will too! The huge window in the ceiling fills the kitchen-living room with light. The quiet, leafy street is full of potted plants and bicycles. My favourite time to relax on the roof terrace is at the end of the day, with the windmill against the sunset. The neighbourhood is a great choice for a stay in Amsterdam – shops, bars, cafes and restaurants, away from the touristy areas but easy by tram to the city centre.

The space
The living room and kitchen at the front has a large wooden table and comfy sofa. It’s not luxurious, but is well-equipped, renovated, clean and fresh, and has a lovely atmosphere. There’s a gas hob and extractor, a combined oven and microwave, dishwasher, fridge, and a vintage expresso machine that makes great coffee. For the rest, in the cupboards and drawers you’ll find everything else you’re likely to need (this is a home, not just a holiday let). The central heating is controlled by
neighborhood_overview: I’m in the nicest part of the area called the Indische Buurt. The quiet streets of late 19th-century buildings run parallel to the Javastraat, which I think is the nicest, most authentic shopping street in Amsterdam! It’s a total mix – shops with fruit and vegetables spilling out onto the street, cafes from trendy to traditional, creative restaurants, boutiques, bakers, fishmongers, Yemeni and Syrian street food, and a great Italian delicatessen. It’s a short walk to the lively Dappermarkt market, the Oosterpark and Tropenmuseum. Artis Zoo is a little further. The canal area, main museums, and Dam Square are all around 25 minutes by public transport, and quicker by bike.
host_about: I’m a Communication Science student at the University of Amsterdam. I’ve grown up in Amsterdam bilingual English and Dutch, so I’ve always felt international. I love to travel, whether for pleasure or study. I’m lucky enough to live in a lovely apartment in a great neigbourhood, and for limited periods it’s available on Airbnb.

name: FREESTANDING HOUSE - GREEN OASIS IN AMSTERDAM
description:
Our peaceful family house is minutes’ biking distance from the NDSM (known as Amsterdam's creative and artistic area) and different ferries to the city center.

It’s freestanding, with a lovely garden, in the middle of a small public green park. So if you enjoy the sounds of birds but also want to experience city life, this is your place to stay!

The space
Our spacious place offers a well-equipped kitchen in the center of the house, connected to the living and dining area.

On the first floor, you will find three bedrooms, the master (double bed), and two kids' rooms, one for a baby or toddler.
It also has a nice bathroom with a shower and bath and a separate toilet.

The house is surrounded by a lovely garden, situated in a small public green area.

Guest access
The place will be completely yours!

Other things to note
Please don't hesitate the get in touch if you have any questio
neighborhood_overview:
Although the neighborhood is super quiet, we have a great coffee and awesome beer spot just a few minutes from our place, different playgrounds, and a simple but nice public paddling pool.

The NDSM offers many amazing restaurants, museums, and exciting places to visit. Within 15 minutes of biking + ferry, you will be at Central Station to explore all the other things Amsterdam offers.

We’re happy to provide you with a list of local go-to’s, as we love discovering new places.
host_about:
We love living in Amsterdam, as it’s one of the best cities of the world. It’s tinny, beatiful, creative and lively. We like to go for a drink & dinner with friends and family, or dance on one of the million festivals we have.

We also love to travel. To discover, to lie on the beach, to dive, to shop, to read all the books that haven’t been opened at home.  And we love the anticipatory pleasure of searching for the most special, nicest, greatest places arround the world to stay. 

We hope you feel comfortable in our vintage and creative home, to relaxe during your stay in one of the best parts of the city, like we do when we’re traveling.

name: Cozy house with green garden near Amsterdam centre
description:
This cozy apartment is located in the hippest neighbourhood: Amsterdam Noord. In the area you will find many supermarkets, restaurants and cafes. Or enjoy our sunny garden with a fresh cup of coffee. Explore all the architecture and hangouts and escape the crowds of the city centre. Amsterdam centre is just a 5 min walk to the metro away or take the bike and cross the river with the free ferry (every 5 min) and go to neighbourhoods like the Jordaan and the Wallen with its famous canals.

The space
The apartment has one bedroom with a comfortable double bed and an extra room with a sleepsofa. The extra room also has an adjustable desk and comfy office chair for working. Furthermore there is a kitchen, bathroom and toilet. There is a private garden in the back and a childfriendly playground in the front.

License number
0363 76C9 B370 17BB 446E
neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam Noord, a quick free ferry ride across the IJ River from central Amsterdam, is a previously neglected area that has been reinvented as the city's hippest neighbourhood. It encompasses ex-industrial areas, cutting-edge architecture, and hangars turned hipster hangouts with walls covered in street art, all minutes away from fields, horses and the odd windmill. Noord is perfect for exploring by bike, stopping to eat and drink in its alternative venues. It's a great area to escape the crowds of central Amsterdam, too.
host_about:
Hi! My name is Jaleesa. I live together with Marty in the beautiful Amsterdam North. Everyday when I bike from my office in the city center back home, I am enjoing the 5 minute ferry ride crossing the river IJ. Leaving the hectic city center behind, enjoing the Amsterdam Skyline and arriving in the unique Amsterdam North. As I work for the municipality, I am - offcourse - proud of my city and I love to share it with my Airbnb guests. 

I love to walk around the area (especially Noorderpark), sip a glass of wine in the afternoon sun in our backyard, have a coffee at the local cafees and I love to visit the Van der Pek Market. 

My other passions are food, gardening, travelling, discover new cultures and meeting new people.

The Albert Cuyp market is a 5-minute walk away and is one of the oldest streetmarkets in Amsterdam, you can find everything from food to nice jewelry, from plant shops to furniture stores.
In addition to the market and the shops, there is also a park where you can work-out or have a picnic.
De Pijp is located just outside the busy citycenter, but it is also just a 20-minute walk away. You could take a nice walk on the famous canals and you can easily reach the city center and the redlight district (this is a little further away).

The convenient location of the apartment means that you can easily reach well-known museums such as the Rijksmuseum where "the Night Watch" is located, or the Van Gogh museum, by public transport, or about a 20-minute walk. Amsterdam Oud-Zuid is one of the most desirable residential neighbourhoods with fancy shopping streets, world-famous museums and a beautiful city park.

Highlights
The prosperous city district of Oud-Zuid (Old South), part of the borough Zuid, has the city's most fashionable shopping streets: PC Hooftstraat, Van Baerlestraat and Beethovenstraat. Don't miss Cornelis Schuytstraat and its trendy boutiques and home stores for a special Dutch outfit or gift.

Top attractions
On Museumplein (Museum Quarter), which belongs to Oud-Zuid, you'll find all top museums close to each other: Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh Museum, Stedelijk Museum, Moco Museum and Diamond Museum.

Other big attractions in this posh district are the Vondelpark and Concertgebouw.

name: Gezellige woonboot met open haard hartje Jordaan.
description:
Our houseboat is located in the heart of the Jordaan, Amsterdam. It is a schark, an ark on a ship :-) A unique experience to visit Amsterdam and staying on the canal. The boat is very light because of the many windows and sliding doors. Besides that you are in the centre, the canal is fortunately not that busy with tourboats. All amenities, such as shops, restaurants, terraces, and parks are within walking distance, just around the corner.

The space
The boat has been completely renovated and has a lovely sitting pit to read a book or watch TV in a relaxed manner. In winter, the underfloor heating keeps you warm and in summer the insulated roof (sedum roof) keeps the boat cool.
The kitchen is fully equipped and the 3-meter-long dining table provides plenty of space for extensive dining.
There are 2 lockable bedrooms. In the morning you wake up and see swans, ducks, and geese swimming past your window.

License number
0363 C5D4 058A
neighborhood_overview:
The filled-in canal in front of the boat is a wonderful place to sit and take in the neighborhood. There you can also play table tennis and the children have their own playground. On the same canal is a small cozy café and a nice Italian restaurant. In any case, the Jordaan is a neighborhood with many bars and restaurants.
On Monday there is a fabric and curios market and on Saturday a food market (with an organic and regular range of food).
After a few minutes walk you are on the Haarlemmerstraat with nice shops. The Westerpark is within walking distance and offers, in addition to the opportunity to run a round, also a lot of cafes and restaurants.
A tram (2 min walk from the boat) or 30 minutes walk takes you to all the famous museums, like the van Gogh and Rijksmuseum.

description:
During our holidays, we would like to rent out our lovely apartment to those who want to explore the city of Amsterdam and its surroundings.

The apartment is on the ground floor and souterrain and is in the central but quiet 'Kadijken' neighbourhood (1 km from Central station), which is known as one of the most beautiful neighbourhoods of Amsterdam.

We hope you enjoy it as much as we do, but please keep the following rules in mind:
- No parties and/or drugs
- No (loud) music
- No pets

The space
Lovely, bright, spacious apartment spread over two floors (76 m2, ground floor and souterrain).

The upper floor exists of a dining area, kitchen and sitting area:
- Kitchen has a big stove with 2 ovens and 6 fires, refrigerator, dishwasher, Quooker tap (boiling water straight from the tap),
- 50 inch flatscreen tv
- Bolia Noora couch, which sits 3 people
- Free WiFi internet connection
- Relax o
neighborhood_overview:
Stay in the heart of Amsterdam and experience how it is to live like a real 'Amsterdammer'. Step outside of the door and enjoy some of the most stunning views of the Amsterdam canals.

We love the neighbourhood with its museums, nice restaurants and bars. Around the corner you can enjoy the best brunch of Amsterdam at Bakers & Roasters, go for a beer and 'bitterballen' at Orloff, have some amazing wood-oven pizza at Sotto, enjoy delicious Indonesian food at Cafe Kadijk or go for a fancy high-end dinner at restaurant Entrepot. All within 50 meters from the apartment!

Although the neighbourhood is centrally located, it is known as a 'little village' in Amsterdam due to its quiet atmosphere and social people. If you want to really experience Amsterdam, there is no better place to stay.

neighborhood_overview:
AMSTERDAM CENTRUM - CITY CENTER + CANAL DISTRICT
In addition to the world-famous historic Canal Ring, Amsterdam's City Centre district ('Centrum') is home to a host of renowned museums, charming and high-end shopping areas, fantastic culture and entertainment.

Amsterdam’s renowned art and culture and top shopping
In Amsterdam’s centre you will, of course, find the magnificent Canal Ring, but there is so much more besides. The inner city, for instance, is bursting with interesting museums, sometimes hidden behind beautiful canal-side façades. The diversity of the city centre’s culture is vast, from the emotional Anne Frank House in the west of the centre, through to the upbeat nature of Science Center NEMO in the east. In between, find an inspiring collection of art and history.

Top shopping
There is a vast array of shopping opportunities, from fashion brands and chains (Nieuwendijk, Kalverstraat) through to independent innovators and inspiring marke

neighborhood_overview:
*The area:
You will find this bright, well-arranged apartment in the popular Indian neighborhood in Amsterdam East. The area has undergone a major transformation in recent years. Many facilities have been added, making it even better to be here!
You can go to a diverse range of nice bars and restaurants such as Wilde Zwijnen, Superette, Hartje Oost, Bar Basquiat, Drovers Dog, Walters, Studio K, Wilde Zwijnen, and of course, Brouwerij 't IJ.
You can do your daily shopping at various supermarkets around the corner ( Javastraat) and the daily Dappermarkt (Monday-Saturday). The neighborhood also has two city parks (Flevopark, opposite of the house, and Oosterpark) and a shopping area (Oostpoort). There are excellent tram and bus connections in front of the house, with Muiderpoort train station a few minutes walk away. The A10 ring road is also an 8-minute drive away, and you can park in front of the door ( paid parking). In short, a fantastic place to be!

neighborhood_overview:

There is a tramstop and metro station in two minutes walking distance, and parking places in front (paid parking).

De Pijp is brimming with fantastic (typical Dutch) cafés, restaurants, coffee shops and bars. Of course, a visit to Amsterdam wouldn’t be the same without a trip to the famous Albert Cuypmarket, flanked by over 100 shops. If you wander down Albert Cuypstraat and Ferdinand Bolstraat, the main streets in de Pijp, you'll find many exotic and authentic Syrian, Moroccan, Surinamese restaurants, to name but a few, and a typical Amsterdam pub is located on almost every corner. Also in abundance are the Islamic butchers, Surinamese, Spanish, Indian and Turkish delicatessens and grocery stores.
Here is a list of some of the attractions within walking distance;

neighborhood_overview:
Het appartement ligt ten westen van het centrum, in de wijk 'De Baarsjes' aan de rand van de prachtige Jordaan.

Het biedt een geweldig toevluchtsoord van de drukke straten van het stadscentrum, maar je bent niet ver weg: er zijn tal van bussen en trams in de buurt om je overal in Amsterdam te brengen. In 10 minuten fietsen of tram, of 20/30 minuten te voet sta je midden in het stadscentrum (met de Jordaan nog dichterbij).

Om de hoek zijn er veel cafés, restaurants, bakkerijen, kleine winkels, een grote supermarkt en espressobars. Ook ben je op loopafstand van zowel het Erasmuspark als het Westerpark (met een bioscoop, restaurants en cafés) en van "de Hallen" (met een bioscoop, winkels, eetgelegenheden, enz.).

Als je het strand wilt bezoeken ben je aan de perfecte kant van Amsterdam: het duurt in totaal ongeveer 45 minuten om van het appartement naar het strand van Zandvoort aan Zee te reizen.

Although it is in the center of Amsterdam, it is fully occupied by locals living there.

The space

Through the shared staircase (with one other household) you enter this beautiful apartment in the hall, from where you enter the li
neighborhood_overview:
History of the building

The building was designed by the famous architect Gerrit van Arkel (1858-1918). The special details such as the facade with its bay windows and the special roof construction with stepped gables on both sides make this property very unique. Due to its virtually unaltered state, the building occupies an important place in the oeuvre of the architect, but also in the history of Amsterdam architecture in relation to the design and the many visible original elements. The building called "Johanna House" is named after the wife of the first residents (Fam. M. Messchaert).


Neighborhood

The building is conveniently located at the foot of Vondelpark. The property is within walking distance of the most luxurious shopping streets (including P.C Hooftstraat, Van Baerlestraat), theaters (including De la Mar, Concertgebouw and cinema), museums (Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh, Stedelijk), nightlife and several restaurants. name: Unieke Historische Woonboot In Amsterdam
description:
Opzoek naar een onvergetelijke ervaring in Amsterdam? Kom gezellig logeren op onze net nieuw gebouwde woonboot. Wij bieden een heerlijke rustige ruimte aan waar je alles voor jezelf hebt en je eigen entree hebt. Het schip ligt in Amsterdam Oost in een gezellige bruisende buurt, en toch vlakbij het centrum. Wanneer je op het schip staat heb je een prachtig uitzicht over de haven en drink je wat op je eigen terras. Leen onze fietsen en ontdek de bruisende binnenstad waar je in 10 min bent.

The space
Ons schip is een replica van een historisch Amsterdams schip uit 1900 en is helemaal nieuw gebouwd in 2022. Het schip is 40 meter lang en ligt in het schoonste buitenzwemwater van Amsterdam vlak naast een van de populairste zwemsteigers van de stad. Door de nieuwbouw combineren we karakteristiek wonen met duurzaam gebruik van onze omgeving. Het hele schip inclusief de B&B is zelfvoorzienend door middel van zonnepanelen en een warmtepomp.

De woonruimte is 40m
host_about:
Hoi! Wij zijn Bas en Barbara, een altijd druk en bezig stel. Ons team van 4 wordt compleet gemaakt door onze twee kleuters. We hebben onze eigen onderneming hier in de buurt. 

Afgelopen zomer hebben we ons 10 jarig jubileum in Amsterdam gevierd. Vanaf onze verhuizing naar Amsterdam hebben we altijd een plek in ons huis gehad voor Airbnb, om op deze manier meer ruimte te creeëren voor onze dromen. Onze laatste en grootste droom, een woonboot midden in Amsterdam, heeft ook weer plek om gasten te ontvangen, ieder in onze eigen privacy.

name: Cosy Canal Houseboat
description:
You do you in Amsterdam. This cosy houseboat is located at one of the most cosy and lively neighbourhoods of Amsterdam. Within a few minutes walk you wander around the Royal Palace at the Dam Square, dive into the history at Anne Frank Museum, see the beautiful nature in the Vondelpark or have a good coffee and tasty apple pie at the local northern market

The space
The houseboat is located in a beautiful canal and gives you the opportunity to really experience Amsterdam. When you stay in this houseboat; it’s completely yours. The houseboat houses a spacious living room, kitchen, comfortable double bed in a private bedroom, bathroom with bath tub and a separate toilet.

The living room has a 4 person dining table and a well equipped kitchen. Don’t feel like cooking? There are plenty of nice restaurants for breakfast, lunch and dinner in the neighbourhood. Ask me about it and I’ll show you some hidden gems.

The bedroom has a double bed. The ba
neighborhood_overview:
The houseboat is located next to the Jordaan. This is possibly the most famous neighbourhood in the Netherlands. In the past the neighbourhood was knows for its tight community bonds, radical politics and a love for drink and over-the-top sing-a-longs.

Gentrification of decades past has attracted more galleries, restaurants, specialty shops. Just outside the door of this apartment you will find supermarkets, many different restaurants, the nine streets to go shopping, the Anne Frank Museum, an antique market, local farmers market (Saturday), the Western Church and the gay monument.

The Vondelpark, Dam Square, Rijks Museum, Stedelijk Museum, Van Gogh Museum, Leidseplein are all within a walking distance of 15-20 minutes.

We are born and raised in the Netherlands and love to travel and meet people from different cultural backgrounds. 

You can contact us in Dutch (native), English (professional), German (limited) and Spanish (limited).

neighborhood_overview:
The studio is located perfectly in vibrant area 'De Pijp'. On the left is the romantic Sarphatipark, with in its 'Liefdesbruggetje' (lovers bridge).
Since 1880 lovers would show each other, and the neighbourhood, that they are an item. To the right is the Albert Cuyp market, Hollands longest market.

'De Pijp' is without doubt a melting pot of cultures and nationalities. It is brimming with fantastic cafés, culinary restaurants, coffee shops, supermarkets and bars. A heaven for foodies!
The nearest supermarket, Albert Heijn, is a 2 minute walk.

Within walking distance from the studio you will find popular sites such as the Heineken Museum, the Van Gogh Museum, The Stedelijk museum, Vondelpark, The Royal Concert hall, Paradiso, Leidseplein and the Rijksmuseum. There is also a canal cruise dock opposite the Heineken Museum. The city center is a 15 minute walk away.

The studio is also close to RAI conference center.

Please have a look

name: 18th Century Groundfloor Canal House with patio
description:
With its picturesque canal view, rich history and modern design, this 2 floor house is a unique city destination. Each area of Amsterdam has its own character and charm. This listed monument dating back to the 18th century, and completely renovated, is truly a quiet retreat and a hidden treasure. Situated directly in the heart of the city, the oldest and most beautiful part of town, this canal house is part of Amsterdam’s iconic Canal Ring and listed as a UNESCO’s World Heritage Site. 

The space
“Home away from home” as our guests would say. Two floors of pure luxury in a great amount of privacy. The main entrance is at the charming Singel canal side. The entrance hall with typical high ceilings and authentic marble floor lead you into our spacious living room with lots of natural daylight and a private patio at the back side of the house. Connecting to the modern and well equipped kitchen with dining area at the front of the house, set the ambiance on the ground
neighborhood_overview:
The house is located on one of the major residential canals in the city centre. It is conveniently located near major tram-lines and only steps away from the Anne Frank House, Dam Square and the Jordaan, which is famous for its variety of shops, restaurants and galleries. The major museums: Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh and Stedelijk are within walking distance. Traveling with children? Visit NEMO (the largest science centre in the Netherlands), ARTIS Royal Zoo, Kinderkookcafé in the Vondelpark, Madame Tussauds or outside Amsterdam De Efteling, Dolfinarium or Madurodam. 
“A Narrow Strip of Dutch Cool”
That is what The New York Times called the Herenstraat and surrounded area. The neighbourhood became increasingly trendy (…) the quaint streets of Herenstraat and Prinsenstraat began to buzz with new energy. Trendy bars and innovative restaurants have opened. And a steady march of independent boutiques is turning the area into one of the city’s coolest retail strips.

We hope you have a great stay at one of the most beautiful places in town.

Regards,
Saskia and Michiel

name: Amsterdam Farm Lodge: quircky, old farmers style
description:
Enjoy a very special green setting on the edges of Amsterdam. A sustainable place to stay, to play and to relax. Not too far from the city, yet tranquille and lots off space.

If you come for a drugs vacation, please find another place to stay. This place is not suited for that, we don't allow the use of marihuana at our premesis.

We are not located in the center of Amsterdam, check the location before booking.

Please read our COVID-19 measures in the description beneath.

The space
Spacious ground floor apartment especially suited for families, in a child friendly environment. The 'Amsterdam Farm Lodge' is located on the terrain of the urban farming project 'NoordOogst', a very special place on the edge of Amsterdam, just a few steps away from the hustling and bustling NDSM wharf. But also a lot to see and do on site. Sustainability is important to us, therefore we made use of recycled materials to decorate the place.

Th
neighborhood_overview:
We are on the site of an awesome urban farming project, you'll find fields with crops, pigs, chickens, a restaurant, a veggie take-away, kids daycare, natural play ground, woodworking, natural playground, a beekeeper, a wine yard and a brewery. And plenty of space to play.

The hustling and bustling NDSM wharf with is only 15 minutes away by bike, from here the ferry to Central Station departs. Ten minutes biking to the other side you can find nature area 'het Twiske' where you can swim, bike and hike. Only 10 minutes by foot you can discover the hidden nature area of 'Noorder IJplas'. The Zaanse Schans, IJselmeer, beach and 'bollenstreek' are easy to reach.
host_about: We are a couple from Amsterdam and we love to travel. A few years ago we've hosted a wintersport chalet in Austria. We liked it so much that we wanted to open our own B&B. What started out with the idea of a small cabin in the backyard, became much bigger when we got the opportunity of opening the Amsterdam Farm Lodge at the urban farming project of NoordOogst. The Amsterdam Farm Lodge is a project for 10 years and it consists of 7 holiday apartments. Let the adventure begin....

I'm a bit all over the place.
I'm born in Rome in 1974, studied graphic design in Milan and moved to Amsterdam (graphic design's world capital) in 2004. I am now a Dutch citizen, I have two kids who are half Swedish and I'm some sort of 'Honorary Citizen' of Catalonia, due to my lovely 'buen retiro' in Barcelona, the Capital of the Mediterranean, the most advanced, exciting and complete town of the whole Southern Europe.

When I travel (and I do love to travel) I always tend to stay in apartments. I wanna live like a local, feel things like the locals feel, buy a recipe book and cook local specialties on the spot and of course feel at home.

And that is what I wanna transmit to my guests too. Renting out houses to tourists is a big responsibility. They have been waiting for months, maybe years for this holiday and you can't simply let them down with an accommodation which is less than great. So I make sure that the apartment is always tiptop, and I really love doing it.
Going to my apartment and always leaving it better than I've found it is my great challenge and pleasure, but I feel that there is not so much left to improve now!

name: Modern & Bright, 2BRM + Canal View @Jordaan area
description:
Modern & bright apartment with beautiful canal view. Very spacious with two bedrooms and a fully equipped open plan kitchen. A large balcony with a view on a "schuilkerk" (shelter church). Enjoy this comfortable home and a typical Amsterdam experience. There's an elevator in the building so you don't have to climb those steep Amsterdam stairs ;-). Very close to the Jordaan & Westerpark with it's cultural hotspots. Easy to reach. Lot's of nice shops, bars & restaurants within walking distance!

The space
Beautiful entrance, possibility to use an elevator up to the third floor where the apartment is. Two bedrooms, one has a regular queensize bed. The guest room has a sleeping couch. All regular kitchen appliances are present (Oven, microwave, water boiler, Nespresso machine etc.) Free & fast WiFi.
I'm sure you will enjoy your stay at my place.

Guest access
You will have the house to yourself. Nothing is shared.

Other things
neighborhood_overview:
The Jordaan is just around the corner, as is Westerpark for great nightlife and sunny days (best coffee at Espressofabriek). Hugo de Grootplein has nice restaurants (my favorites are 'Morgan en Mees' and Razmataz). For take out, try the Thai in the little shed on the bridge (the nicest people with great fresh food).

Closest supermarket is just around the corner (Dirk van den Broek: Tweede Nassaukade) moreover 4 Albert Heijns are within walking distance.
host_about:

Best,

Steven

name: Very cool & quaint 3-story home and roof terrace
description:
This beautiful 3-story historical house, located in the heart of Amsterdam, has recently been completely renovated. The spacious living-room with its gorgeous interior design, high ceilings and fully equipped kitchen, is located on ground level. On the first floor you'll find two cosy (children) bedrooms, as well as the stylish bathroom with a rain-shower and separate bathtub. The master bedroom is located on the top floor. It's light, spacious and gives access to the large and sunny terrace.

The space
The house is fully renovated in 2017 and lives up to all modern standards, even though the building dates from the late 17th century. High-speed wireless internet, a built-in speakers system, fully equipped kitchen and floor heating are just a few of its amenities. You'll find full comfort in this warm and cosy home for you and your friends/family. Besides the master bedroom on the top floor, the house has two separate bedrooms, suitable for children to grown-ups.<
neighborhood_overview: The Jordaan is possibly the most famous neighbourhood in the Netherlands. This once working-class bastion was renowned for tight community bonds, radical politics and a love for drink and over-the-top sing-a-longs. Gentrification of decades past has attracted more galleries, restaurants, specialty shops and upwardly-mobile residents to its scenic streets, but there’s undeniably still a distinct atmosphere to be enjoyed here.
host_about: Hello, I am Peter Bas. Together with my young family I live in the historic city centre of Amsterdam, called De Jordaan. We love to travel and when we are away we offer our lovely house to people who want to explore the exciting city of Amsterdam.

name: Private Studio on Spectacular Houseboat
description:
We were able to build our dream. A unique, modern and comfortable houseboat of 35 x 6 meters. We designed an independent private studio in the bow of the boat that can be your's for a few days. So you can share our experience of living the good life on the water. My husband Michael and I live on the other side of the boat.

The space
The nautical boutique style studio is situated in the bow of houseboat "Tasmania". You get your own private space with a private entrance and en-suite bathroom with great shower and toilet. It has underfloor heating and is cosy and warm in the wintertime.

From the bed, you can look at the stars or the full moon. On the private deck you can enjoy a glass of wine and watch the sunset and the beautiful row of old seventeenth century warehouses.
The Tasmania lies at the edge of the city centre in the old woodharbor, a secret hideaway just around the corner of the bustling city centre. Quiet and beautiful, it is situated i
neighborhood_overview: We live in a sheltered harbour just minutes away from the city centre. In the summer we see the sun rise on the port side and the sun set on the starboard side. You can enjoy the sun here alle day. We swim here all summer long and paddle our kayaks. There is also a lot of paddle boarding going on (we don't own one) and lot's of mall boats passing by. There are 2 electrical boat rentals very nearby.
host_about:
Many guests have asked: "What was this boat before you reconverted it?" The answer is simple: it didn't exist. It was custom build. In October 2011 the "Tasmania" arrived in Amsterdam. Our dream came true and we would love to share that dream with you. 

We are hard working film and television professionals. Before building this boat we used to travel a lot. Now every day feels like a holiday. When we are at home we'll be happy to welcome you and tell you everything you want to know about Amsterdam and the boat. But most of the time we're out working. It will make your stay more private. We hope the studio apartment appeals to people who like to travel independent, just like us.

Favorite travel destination: Namibia
Favorite movies: De Rouille et d'Os, Heat, Das Weisse Band and many more.
Favorite Filmfestival: International Documentary Festival Amsterdam (IDFA)
Favorite Music Festivals: Amsterdam Dance Event, North Sea Jazz Festival
Favorite books: Story of a Life by Paustovsky, Innumeracy by Paulos
Favorite food: Mediterranean
Favorite drink: wine, wine, wine. Soon finishing studies at the Wineacademy

neighborhood_overview:
Amsterdam North is an upcoming area, with pop up stores and art projects. The area is nice and quiet with a big park 3 minutes walk, with a wooden playground and a good coffee bar. There is a whole range of shops and supermarkets about 5 mins walking and an open market on Wednesday, Friday and Saturday.
The house is near the newly opened EYE film museum, which has become a must see, and place to have coffee looking over the water, and is surrounded by the Tolhuistuin cafe and the Amsterdam Look Out

Parking: You can park in front of the house. They are currently introducing paid parking. We don't know exactly when it will start now it's free.
Public Transport: Well served by buses, Line 34 and 35 which take you to central station in 5 minutes, they come every 5 minutes too. Or the new metro, North South line. From there you can go anywhere such as the Dam, the Jordaan shopping area, the museum area via tram 2 or 5 which takes 10 minutes from central station.

Our happy home has a small and very sunny bedroom upstairs with a queen size bed, which leads to a wonderful double deck roof terrace full of bright well kept flowers and plants in the summer time. host_about:
Hi Airbnb-ers, 
Welcome on my profile page, I am an easy going guy living in downtown Amsterdam. In the middle of it all, yet in in a quiet street. I love to travel and like to meet new people from all over the world! Airbnb is a great community and I am extremely proud they awarded me with the superhost status. I will do the utmost to make you feel comfortable. Besides giving massage I like food, dance, food, theatre, food, coffee, did I say food? ;-)

I have 2 B&B rooms (renovated in February ‘18) I would love to have you as my guest! (yes I also run a massage center, and yes you get a discount!) In the very heart of Amsterdam.

I have an official B&B so no need to worry you stay somewhere illegal as the press is lately not so kind to Airbnb.

neighborhood_overview:
Museum Quarter Attractions
Located near the Museumplein, the Museum District (Museumkwartier) is certainly the place for culture vultures to be in Amsterdam. The quarter is home to the Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh Museum, Stedelijk Museum, Concertgebouw (Concert Hall) and the Vondelpark. If that’s not enough, then there’s also Coster Diamonds, which gives free tours of its factory, to amuse and amaze you. Most of the buildings in this attractive quarter are from the 19th century and both Museumplein and Vondelpark are great for picnics and relaxing on the grass.

Museum Quarter Shopping

The apartment is located in one of the famous ‘canal’ houses at the Brouwersgracht, which has once been voted as one of the most beautiful canals in Amsterdam. The apartment is on the first floor and offers an excellent view on the canal. You will also have access to the garden.

The space
The space is a comfortable Amsterdam apartment, located in the Jordaan. The Jordaan is the neighborhood where most ‘Amsterdammers’ want to live as it is one of the most popular and charming area’s in the city. The Jordaan is especially known for its beautiful canals, historic buildings and relaxed atmosphere. The Jordaan offers, among others, a huge variety of small local shops, cafes, restaurants and even a local market on Mondays and Saturdays just around the corner. It’s the perfect place in the centre of Amsterdam with a village-like vibe.

A beautiful apartment ideal for people who are looking for a special spot. The location is central and adjacent to one of the nicest squares in Amsterdam, close to the famous “Jordaan” district.

We wish you a pleasant stay and look forward to welcoming you!

The space
Many canalhouses are facing just one canal. This one is facing two. One canal in the front and one at the side. Situated at what is called "Little Venice" this light and bright appartment with many windows offers all comfort you'll search for in Amsterdam.

Because the appartment is situated in a bend of the canal, you'll experience an extraordinary view that oversees 5 bridges and over 750 metres (0,5 miles). But above all, the apartment is situated as central as you can be in the city with the famous 9 streets on the corner, the famous 9 bridges in 1 minutes walk and the well known shoppingstreets 'Kalverstraat' and 'Leidschestraat' on the other corner.

There are many, many, really many.

The room is equipped with a luxury king size hotel box-spring bed on which you can enjoy a good night's sleep after a long day in the city. The room is furnished with a writing table and various built-in cupboards and TV with Netflix. The room includes a private en-suite shower-room. neighborhood_overview: The building is located in Amsterdam centre in the popular Jordaan district.  The area is famous for it's idyllic streets full with small unique shops, many bars and restaurants. The Anne Frank house is just around the corner next to the century old Westerchurch. Once outside you find yourself immediately in between the 17th century canals and you can start your walking tour or try one of the tour boats. Dam square, the red light district, the 9-streets, parks, museums and nightlife are all walking distrance. Trams and taxis are footsteps away as are several bike rentals.
host_about:
Hi, my name is Marcel and I live in the centre of Amsterdam in between the historic canals, the Dam square, the Anne Frank House and the famous Jordaan. Surrounded with restaurants, terraces and shops this is one if the best locations in the city, because it’s in the middle of where all happens yet in a quiet street. In my house I offer two double bed & coffee rooms each with a private shower and one room even with a bath. I live in the building and I have my own bathroom. A bed & coffee room means your rent a b&b room, but instead of breakfast with unlimited coffee and tea that you make with your own Nespresso maker. The building offers a pretty unique large roof terrace that is magically lit by night. 

I'm a foody and spend much of my time cooking, going to the local markets and enjoy restaurants. If you need some advise where to go or what to eat please ask!

In my home I offer my guests privacy. But please knock my door for questions or a chat any time and most likely we’ll meet on the terrace anyway ;)

Enjoying a city like Amsterdam is all about having a place where you feel comfortable and safe at home in a strange environment. And especially to have a good bed, a warm shower and a nice cup of coffee or tea with a stroopwafel at any time you like. In my travels I visit and visited a lot of B&B's globally. Staying in a room in somebody’s home often felt I was staying with friends. Some of them became and still are dear friends after many years. This experience is what I try to offer my guests. Live like a local, feel at home. Tot ziens in Amsterdam, Marcel.

B&B Lisenced by council of Amsterdam.

neighborhood_overview:
Museum Quarter Attractions
Located near the Museumplein, the Museum District (Museumkwartier) is certainly the place for culture vultures to be in Amsterdam. The quarter is home to the Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh Museum, Stedelijk Museum, Concertgebouw (Concert Hall) and the Vondelpark. If that’s not enough, then there’s also Coster Diamonds, which gives free tours of its factory, to amuse and amaze you. Most of the buildings in this attractive quarter are from the 19th century and both Museumplein and Vondelpark are great for picnics and relaxing on the grass.

Museum Quarter Shopping
Put your sunglasses on and polish-up your credit card - the Museum District's shops are frequented by the Dutch glitterati and are as excellent for entertainment value as they are for finding a new pair of designer shoes. name: Sleeping in a unique ship in the center of A'dam!
description:
Thank you for finding me. I offer you an unique recently rebuild place in the centre of Amsterdam. Your cosy apartment has a private entrance so there is no customer contact.

Although the Keizerinn BnB is located in a quiet neighborhood, you will find lots of small bars and restaurants in the direct surroundings.

The space
You will stay on a unique ship type "Groninger Bol"which is completely renovated by Peter the owner. The ship, which is built in 1904, used to be an cargo ship in those days. Peter left the original details of the ship to make your stay one kind of it's own.

The Keizerinn is very well isolated and uses the most modern environmental friendly techniques to reduce your carbon steps! The floor heating gives the apartment a nice warmth, especially in winter time it will keep you feet nice and warm.

You can have a cosy seat in the original wheelhouse and when it is nice weather you can site on your own terrace on top
neighborhood_overview:
The Keizerinn BnB is located in one of the oldest greenest parts of Amsterdam. You will find a lot of history here. Within 50 meters you will find one of the oldest Hortus Botanicus from the world which is grounded is the year 1682. You can enjoy nature all around the year on your own terrace.

There are also some famous WW2 locations: De Joodsche schouwburg, het Verzetsmuseum and in the Wertheims park you can find the Auschwitz monument.
host_about:
Welcome on my boat!

I'm  offering you a wonderfull stay at one of Amsterdams most beautifull spots.

As a technical allrounder (I can fix nearly everything) is the reason that I was able to renovate this boat myself (with a little help from my friends :-)). The ship is originally build in 1904 and is a so called "Groninger Bol ship”. Although the ship is more than 100 years old, I modernised it to todays standards with keeping the authentic details.

I hope that you will enjoy your stay with me. And I am happy to inform you about everything Amsterdam has to offer.

Warm regards,

Peter.
